Title : Robert Laughlin Pierson
Text : '''Robert Laughlin Pierson''' (1926â€“1997) was an Episcopal clergyman and [[Freedom Rider]].

==Life==
He was born in [[Chicago]] in 1926.
He graduated from [[Lawrence University]], the [[University of Wisconsin]], and [[Nashotah House]].<ref name="Saxon">{{cite news|last=Saxon|first=Wolfgang|title=Robert Pierson, Episcopal Priest, 71, Is Dead|work=The New York Times|page=10|date=29 April 1997|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/04/29/nyregion/robert-pierson-episcopal-priest-71-is-dead.html}}</ref>

He served at [[St. Barnabas' Episcopal Church (Newark, New Jersey)|St. Barnabas' Episcopal Church]].
In 1961, he was arrested at [[Jackson, Mississippi]], with the [[Freedom Riders]].<ref name="Saxon" />

He died on April 13, 1997, in [[St. Petersburg, Florida]].<ref name="Saxon" />  

==Family==
He married Ann Clark Rockefeller in 1955; they divorced in 1966.<ref name="Saxon" /> 

